ches metadata: doc_id, filename, source, page Cleans whitespace and filters empty pages Saves uploaded PDFs to backend/storage/uploads/ Key API Endpoints 5. Phase 3 — Chunking Strategi', '/ Key API Endpoints 5. Phase 3 — Chunking Strategies Four chunking strategies were implemented, all selectable from the frontend dropdown.', 'Chunker 1 — Recursive Character Text Splitter File: backend/ingestion/chunker.py   Mode: recursive Uses LangChain RecursiveCharacterTextSplitter Splits on \\n\\n → \\n → . → space (priority order) Default: chunk_size=500, chunk_overlap=50 Best for: general documents, fast processing Chunker 2 — Semantic Chunker File: backend/ingestion/semantic_chunker.py   Mode: semantic Splits sentences, embeds each with text-embedding-3-small Computes cosine distance between consecutive sentence embeddings Splits', 'nce between consecutive sentence embeddings Splits where semantic distance exceeds breakpoint_threshold=0.3', 'Uses a buffer_size=1 window for smoothing Best for: multi-topic documents, technical notes Chunker 3 — Sliding Window File: backend/ingestion/sliding_window.py   Mode: sliding Fixed-size windows with configurable overlap Formula: step = chunk_size - chunk_overlap Stores window_start and window_end in metadata Best for: dense text where no context should be lost at boundaries Chunker 4 — Fixed Size File: backend/ingestion/fixed_chunker.py   Mode: fixed Hard splits at exact character count — no ov', 'fixed Hard splits at exact character count — no overlap Stores start_index and end_index in metadata', 'Best for: uniform processing, structured documents Chunking Mode Selection Selected per-upload from the frontend dropdown — sent as chunk_mode field in FormData. Backend selects chunker dynamically via get_chunker(mode) factory function. 6. Phase 4 — Embedding & Vector Store Embedder — backend/ingestion/embedder.py Vector Store — backend/ingestion/vector_store.py ChromaDB Configuration Collection name: pdf_rag Distance metric: cosine (via hnsw:space) Persistence directory: backend/storage/chroma', 'ace) Persistence directory: backend/storage/chroma_db/ Each chunk stored with: text, filename, doc_id, chunk_index, page, chunk_type', 'Delete Functionality vector_store.delete_by_filename(filename) queries ChromaDB by filename metadata field Returns count of deleted vectors Frontend shows 🗑️ button per file — sends POST /delete with filename 7. Phase 5 — Retrieval & Query Pipeline Retriever — backend/retrieval/retriever.py Evolution of Retrieval Strategy Current Logic (v4 — Adaptive) Behaviour Examples: Query about Google → only Google chunks retrieved Query comparing all companies → all docs included Query about Apple (not upl', 'ies → all docs included Query about Apple (not uploaded) → best available doc, minimal context', 'Generator — backend/generation/generator.py System Prompt 8. Phase 6 — Enterprise Restructure The project was reorganized from a flat layout into a proper enterprise directory structure. Before (Flat Structure) After (Enterprise Structure) 9. Phase 7 — Improvements & Fixes Logging System File: backend/utils/logger.py Structured logs at every pipeline stage Dual output: terminal + rotating log file in backend/logs/ Format: timestamp | LEVEL | module | message Answer Formatting Markdown rendering:', 'le | message Answer Formatting Markdown rendering: ## headers, bold, italic, bullets, inline code', 'MathJax integration: LaTeX expressions rendered as proper math (e.g. U = ½ CV²) Expand/collapse cards: Click question header to collapse previous answers Scrollbar & UX Results area: overflow-y: auto with min-height: 0 (flex scroll fix) Sidebar: independently scrollable Dark-themed custom scrollbar across all panels Issues Resolved 10. Final File Structure 11. Configuration Reference requirements.txt Environment Variables (.env) Run Command Access: http://localhost:8000 12. Known Limitations & N', 's: http://localhost:8000 12. Known Limitations & Next Steps Current Limitations', 'Recommended Next Steps Pipeline Summary'], 'model': 'text-embedding-3-small', 'encoding_format': 'base64'}}
